Rating: 4
This tart is delicious. I made it for a brunch, thinking that the guests would eat one tart and I'd have the other to take to a party the next day. The brunch guests ended up eating both tarts! I did a couple of things to simplify making the tarts. First, don't bother cutting strips off the bottom pastry. Instead, simply fold up the ends to give you the higher edges you need. Second, use parchment paper under the tarts when you bake them. This makes clean-up much easier. Finally, be careful when you are reducing the maple syrup. Like all sugar, it boils over quickly. I had a huge mess because I wasn't watching carefully.

