Rating: 3
I've made this a couple of different ways now. The first time, I made lots of individual tarts - I cut the pastry into squares (about 3" each side) and then spread on some of the cream cheese mixture and then some sliced raw apple and baked those. Rather nice, but much less effort and yummier the second way: I first cooked the apples with some maple syrup, brandy and spices (cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg). Then I spread the cream cheese mixture on one piece of the pastry and topped with lots of the apple mixture and folded the edges up. Then I used a second piece of pastry as a lid. Wash with egg and put holes in it. Cook for 30 min. I skipped the maple syrup glaze (since I had maple syrup in the cooked apples). Easy and very yummy with vanilla icecream. Tania Duffield http://www.netspace.net.au/~kokopeli